Statistical analysis

design <- model.matrix(~ 0 + group, x$samples)
rownames(design) <- colnames(x)
colnames(design) <- sub("group", "", colnames(design))
design
         KO.Ctl KO.Sti WT.Ctl WT.Sti
KO-1_Ctl      1      0      0      0
KO-1_Sti      0      1      0      0
KO-2_Ctl      1      0      0      0
KO-2_Sti      0      1      0      0
KO-3_Ctl      1      0      0      0
KO-3_Sti      0      1      0      0
WT-1_Ctl      0      0      1      0
WT-1_Sti      0      0      0      1
WT-2_Ctl      0      0      1      0
WT-2_Sti      0      0      0      1
WT-3_Ctl      0      0      1      0
WT-3_Sti      0      0      0      1
attr(,"assign")
[1] 1 1 1 1
attr(,"contrasts")
attr(,"contrasts")$group
[1] "contr.treatment"
v <- voom(x, design, plot = FALSE, save.plot = TRUE)
plot_voom(v)

fit <- lmFit(v, design)
con <- makeContrasts(
  background = (KO.Ctl + KO.Sti) / 2  - (WT.Ctl + WT.Sti) / 2,
  condition = (WT.Sti + KO.Sti) / 2  - (WT.Ctl + KO.Ctl) / 2,
  KO = KO.Sti - KO.Ctl,
  WT = WT.Sti - WT.Ctl,
  Sti = KO.Sti - WT.Sti,
  Ctl = KO.Ctl - WT.Ctl,
  levels = design
)
con
        Contrasts
Levels   background condition KO WT Sti Ctl
  KO.Ctl        0.5      -0.5 -1  0   0   1
  KO.Sti        0.5       0.5  1  0   1   0
  WT.Ctl       -0.5      -0.5  0 -1   0  -1
  WT.Sti       -0.5       0.5  0  1  -1   0
fit2 <- contrasts.fit(fit, con)

fit2 <- eBayes(fit2)
to_tidy(fit2$p.value, "gene", "group", "p.value") %>%
  filter(group != "(Intercept)") %>%
  ggplot(aes(p.value)) +
    geom_histogram(binwidth = .01) + 
    facet_wrap(~group)

topTable(fit2)
top <- topTable(fit2, coef = "Ctl", number = Inf)
head(top)
